  h1 Advisory Board
  ul 
    li.team_bio 
      img title="Bob Glushko" alt="Bob Glushko" src="#{asset_path('team/bob_glushko.gif')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2 Bob Glushko
      h3 
        |Adjunct Full Professor, 
        a href="http://www.ischool.berkeley.edu/" target="_blank" University of California at Berkeley School of Information
      p 
        |Professor Glushko has over thirty years of R&amp;D, consulting, and entrepreneurial experience in information systems and service design, content management, electronic publishing, Internet commerce, and human factors in computing systems. He founded or co-founded four companies, including Veo Systems in 1997, which pioneered the use of XML for electronic business. He has served on the Board of Directors for 
        a href="https://www.oasis-open.org" target="_blank" OASIS
        |, an international consortium that drives the development and adoption of &#8220;open standards for the global information society,&#8221; and is currently on the Board of Directors for the 
        a href="http://www.opendatafoundation.org/" target="_blank" Open Data Foundation
        |, dedicated to the adoption of global metadata standards for statistical data.
    
    li.team_bio 
      img title="Joaquin Alvarado" alt="Joaquin Alvarado" src="#{asset_path('team/joaquin_alvarado.jpeg')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2 Joaquin Alvarado
      h3 
        | Chief Strategy Officer, 
        a href="http://www.cironline.org/" target="_blank" Center for Investigative Reporting
      p 
        | Before joining the Center for Investigative Reporting, Joaquin served as senior vice president for digital innovation at 
        a href="http://www.publicradio.org/" target="_blank" American Public Media 
        | and founding senior vice president for diversity and innovation at the 
        a href="http://www.cpb.org/" target="_blank" Corporation for Public Broadcasting
        |. In 2004, Joaquin began the 
        a href="http://bavc.org/national-public-lightpath-fiber-optics-american-communities" target="_blank" National Public Lightpath
        |, advocating high-speed, fiber-optic network as the next generation of the Internet. Joaquin serves on the boards of 
        a href="http://www.techsoupglobal.org/" target="_blank" TechSoup Global 
        | and 
        a href="http://www.greaterpublic.org/" target="_blank" DEI
        |, the public broadcasting development association.

    li.team_bio
      img title="Kris Carpenter Negulescu" alt="Kris Carpenter Negulescu" src="#{asset_path('team/kris_carpenter.jpeg')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2 Kris Carpenter Negulescu
      h3 
        | Director of the Web Archive, 
        a href="http://www.archive.org/" target="_blank" Internet Archive
      p 
        | Kris works closely with national libraries, archives and universities to provide technical expertise and services in web archiving and web search. Prior to joining the Internet Archive, Kris worked in the high-tech-industry, for-profit sector. For the last 15 years, she divided her time between the online consumer and business-to-business services and software sectors. Kris holds a Master&#8217;s in Organizational Behavior from 
        a href="http://www.stanford.edu/" target="_blank" Stanford University 
        | and has spent the majority of her career in product and general management roles for venture-backed Silicon Valley start-ups.

