  h1 Partner Organizations
  ul    
    li.team_bio 
      a.team_pic href="http://kitchensisters.org" target="_blank"
        img title="The Kitchen Sisters" alt="The Kitchen Sisters" src="#{asset_path('team/kitchen_sisters.png')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2 
        a href="http://kitchensisters.org" target="_blank" The Kitchen Sisters
      p The Kitchen Sisters, award winning producers Davia Nelson and Nikki Silva, have been creating radio together for NPR and public broadcast since 1979. Over three decades their audio collection has grown to over 5000 recordings — an accidental archive documenting the lives and stories of people, well known and unsung. Their stories chronicle the B-side of history: seldom heard voices, immigrant’s stories, little known histories; the traditions and rituals people carry with them from one country to another, across one generation to the next; the vibrant, changing and fading soundtrack of America.   
    
    li.team_bio.no_round 
      a.team_pic href="http://www.knightfoundation.org/" target="_blank"
        img title="Knight Foundation" alt="Knight Foundation" src="#{asset_path('team/knight.png')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2 
        a href="http://www.knightfoundation.org/" target="_blank" John S. and James L. Knight Foundation
      p Knight advances journalism excellence in the digital age, through an array of media innovation projects and other initiatives. The Knight Foundation supports transformational ideas that promote quality journalism, advance media innovation, engage communities and foster the arts. The foundation believes that democracy thrives when people and communities are informed and engaged.
        
    li.team_bio.no_round 
      a.team_pic href="http://neh.gov" target="_blank"
        img title="NEH" alt="NEH" src="#{asset_path('team/neh_logo_horizontal_rgb.jpg')}"
      h2 
        a href="http://neh.gov" target="_blank" The National Endowment for the Humanities
      p   The National Endowment for the Humanities (NEH) is an independent federal agency created in 1965. It is one of the largest funders of humanities programs in the United States. Because democracy demands wisdom, NEH serves and strengthens our republic by promoting excellence in the humanities and conveying the lessons of history to all Americans. The Endowment accomplishes this mission by awarding grants for top-rated proposals examined by panels of independent, external reviewers.
      
    li.team_bio.no_round
      a href="http://archive.org" target="_blank"
        img title="Internet Archive" alt="Internet Archive" src="#{asset_path('team/internet_archive.png')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2
        a href="http://archive.org" target="_blank" Internet Archive
      p 
        | The Internet Archive was founded to build an Internet library with permanent access for researchers, historians, scholars, people with disabilities, and the general public to historical collections that exist in digital format. The Internet Archive is also responsible for the 
        a href="http://web.archive.org/" target="_blank" Wayback Machine
        |, where they store copies of over 240 billion web pages from 1996 to present. Pop Up Archive has collaborated with the Internet Archive as a trusted digital repository since the summer of 2011. Pop Up Archive benefits from the Archive’s robust storage and preservation capabilities, including their commitment to transcoding media as formats evolve over time.
        
    li.team_bio.no_round 
      a.team_pic href="http://www.airmedia.org/" target="_blank"
        img title="AIR" alt="AIR" src="#{asset_path('team/AIR.png')}" width="150" height="150"
      h2 
        a href="http://www.airmedia.org/" target="_blank" Association of Independents in Radio
      p 
        | AIR is a broad and growing network of 900+ media makers, journalists, producers, technologists, and sound artists who represent an important and vital driving force in the media-technology revolution underway.To learn more about AIR and our vibrant community of makers, visit 
        a href="http://www.airmedia.org" target="_blank" www.airmedia.org 
        | or contact us at 
        a href="mailto:join@airmedia.org" target="_blank" join@airmedia.org
        |.
      
    li.team_bio.no_round 
      a.team_pic href="http://www.digitalpreservation.gov/ndsa" target="_blank"
